				<h3>Made for Backers.</h3>
			</a>
		</div>
		<div id="collapse0ne" class="accordian-body collapse">
			<div class="accordian-inner">
				<p>
				Kickstarter isn't a store front. They've made that perfectly clear. If you decide to back a project, there's no guarantee that the reward you are claiming based on your contribution will ever come to fruition.
				</p>
				<p>
				However, our review team can provide you additional data points so that you can understand the logic behind which promises a project creator will likely be able to keep. We examine common factors that have led to historically favorable outcomes for Kickstarter projects. And our review process will only get better as more projects succeed.
				</p>
				<p>
				Clearly, just because our team indicates the existence of certain success factors in a particular project, backers should be aware that the project may still fail. Our team bases their review on publicly available information from a creator's project site and can not verify the validity or comprehensiveness of this information.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
